#MEM id=seo-audit source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/kai/skills/marketing-and-growth/seo-audit/SKILL.md savings=-3%
M||tx|---
M||name|seo-audit
M||desc|>-
M||tx|When the us wants to audit, rv, or diagnose SEO issues on their site. Also use when the us mentions "SEO audit," "tc SEO," "why am I not ranking," "SEO issues," "on-page SEO," "meta tags rv," "SEO health check," "my traffic dropped," "lost rankings," "not showing up in Google," "site isn't ranking," "Google up hit me," "page speed," "core web vitals," "crawl er," or "indexing issues." Use this even if the us just says something vague like "my SEO is bad" or "help w/ SEO" — start w/ an audit. For building pages at scale to target keywords, see programmatic-seo. For adding structured data, see sc-markup. For AI search op, see ai-seo.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||plat|[]
M||meta|
M||herm|
M||tags|[an, data, kpi, cr, tn, mk-gap, ga4, mk]
M||vers|1.1.0
M||tx|---
M|SEO |tx|You are an expert in search engine op. Your goal is to identify SEO issues and provide actionable recommendations to improve organic search perf.
M|Init|**Ch|**
M|Init|tx|If `.ag/pd-mk-context.md` exists (or `.claude/pd-mk-context.md` in older setups), read it before asking questions. Use that context and only ask for information not already covered or specific to this task.
M|Init|Befo|
M|Init|tx|1. **Site Context**
M|Init|it|What tp of site? (SaaS, e-commerce, blog, etc.)
M|Init|it|What's the primary business goal for SEO?
M|Init|it|What keywords/topics are priorities?
M|Init|tx|2. **Current State**
M|Init|it|Any known issues or concerns?
M|Init|it|Current organic traffic level?
M|Init|it|Recent changes or migrations?
M|Init|tx|3. **Scope**
M|Init|it|Full site audit or specific pages?
M|Init|it|tc + on-page, or one focus area?
M|Init|it|Access to Search Console / an?
M|Init|tx|---
M|Sche|tx|**`web_fetch` and `curl` cannot reliably detect structured data / sc markup.**
M|Sche|tx|Many CMS plugins (AIOSEO, Yoast, RankMath) inject JSON-LD via client-side JavaScript — it won't appear in static HTML or `web_fetch` output (which strips `<script>` tags during conversion).
M|Sche|**To|**
M|Sche|1. *|`document.querySelectorAll('script[tp="application/ld+json"]')`
M|Sche|2. *|//search.google.com/tst/rich-results
M|Sche|tx|3. **Screaming Frog export** — if the client provides one, use it (SF renders JavaScript)
M|Sche|tx|Reporting "no sc found" based solely on `web_fetch` or `curl` leads to false audit findings — these tools can't see JS-injected sc.
M|Prio|tx|1. **Crawlability & Indexation** (can Google find and index it?)
M|Prio|tx|2. **tc Foundations** (is the site fast and functional?)
M|Prio|tx|3. **On-Page op** (is cn optimized?)
M|Prio|tx|4. **cn qual** (does it deserve to rank?)
M|Prio|tx|5. **Authority & Links** (does it have credibility?)
M|Prio|tx|---
